{#- ═══ CALC ISLAND — the .calc widget markup is preserved VERBATIM (tb-calc.js binds
    to data-calc / data-calc-input / data-calc-result / data-calc-value|band|why +
    #calc-model JSON — class restyle of the result CTA is behavior-safe). id="calc"
    kept so the hero "Skip to the calculator" anchor still lands. ═══ -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="calc">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">The calculator</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="max-width:24ch;margin-bottom:10px;">Estimate your managed-payroll fee.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:66ch;">Pick the option that fits in each row. The estimate updates as you go. Everything stays in your browser &mdash; nothing is sent until <em>you</em> decide to book a call.</p>

    <div class="calc" data-calc>
      <form class="calc__form" aria-describedby="calc-disclaimer-top">
        <p class="calc__formnote" id="calc-disclaimer-top">Estimates our management fee &mdash; not wages or taxes. Not a quote.</p>
        {%- for field in model.inputs %}
        <div class="calc__field intake-field">
          <label class="intake-field__label" for="calc-{{ field.id }}">{{ field.label | safe }}{% if field.help %} <span class="intake-field__optional">{{ field.help | safe }}</span>{% endif %}</label>
          <select id="calc-{{ field.id }}" data-calc-input="{{ field.id }}">
            {%- for opt in field.options %}
            <option value="{{ opt.v }}">{{ opt.label | safe }}</option>
            {%- endfor %}
          </select>
        </div>
        {%- endfor %}
      </form>

      <div class="calc__result" id="calc-result" role="status" aria-live="polite" data-calc-result>
        <p class="calc__result-label">Estimated management fee</p>
        <p class="calc__result-range"><span data-calc-value>$150&ndash;$300</span><span class="calc__result-unit">/mo</span></p>
        <p class="calc__result-band" data-calc-band>Single-state, small team</p>
        <p class="calc__result-why" data-calc-why>A handful of employees on one pay schedule in a single state.</p>
        <p class="calc__result-disclaimer">This is TechBrot&rsquo;s <strong>management fee</strong> &mdash; an estimate from published pricing, not a quote, and <strong>separate from wages and payroll taxes</strong>. Your exact fixed fee is confirmed in writing within 3 business days of a free discovery call.</p>
        <a class="btn btn-cta calc__result-cta" href="/contact/?intent=payroll" data-ga="cta_click" data-tb-event="calc_to_quote" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:9px;height:50px;padding:0 22px;border-radius:12px;font-size:15px;font-weight:600;">Get your exact fixed fee</a>
      </div>

      <noscript>
        <div class="calc__noscript">
          <p>The live estimate needs JavaScript. You can still see the full published ranges on the <a href="/pricing/">pricing page</a>, or <a href="/contact/?intent=payroll">book a free discovery call</a> for an exact fixed-fee quote within 3 business days.</p>
        </div>
      </noscript>
    </div>

    <script type="application/json" id="calc-model">{{ model | dump | safe }}</script>
  </div>
</section>

{#- ═══ HOW IT'S CALCULATED — no-black-box prose + the four bands as a v2 .cmp table
    (data-col for mobile stacking). sand alt band. ═══ -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="payroll-calc-how" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">No black box</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2">How this estimate is calculated.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 18px;max-width:66ch;">Every number is a slice of our published $150&ndash;$800+/month payroll-management range &mdash; we&rsquo;d rather show the math than hide it.</p>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>TechBrot payroll management is a fixed monthly fee against a written scope &mdash; <strong>$150 to $800+ per month</strong>. To be clear about what that fee is: it&rsquo;s what we charge to <strong>run your payroll</strong> &mdash; calculating pay, filing and depositing payroll taxes, handling multi-state registration and compliance, and producing the reports. It is <strong>not</strong> your wage bill or your tax liability; those are your costs and depend on what you pay your people.</p>
      <p>Our fee scales with the work: headcount, the number of states you run payroll in (multi-state compliance is the biggest driver), pay frequency, and how many contractors need 1099s. The calculator scores those four factors and maps the total to a band inside the published range.</p>
      <p>The estimate is a <strong>range, never a single number</strong>. Two businesses with the same headcount can need different work depending on states, benefits, and how clean the existing setup is. The real fixed fee is set after a ProAdvisor reviews your situation on a free discovery call, and is always delivered in writing before any work begins.</p>
    </div>
    <table class="cmp" style="margin-top:24px;">
      <caption class="sr-only">The four managed-payroll bands inside TechBrot&rsquo;s published $150–$800+/month range.</caption>
      <thead><tr><th scope="col">Band</th><th scope="col">Typical range</th><th scope="col">Looks like</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        {%- for b in model.bands %}
        <tr>
          <th scope="row" data-col="Band">{{ b.name }}</th>
          <td class="num" data-col="Typical range">{{ b.display | safe }}/mo</td>
          <td data-col="Looks like">{{ b.why | safe }}</td>
        </tr>
        {%- endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</section>

